==English==
===Pronunciation===
*kĕt'(ə)l, /ˈket(ə)l/, /<tt>"ket(@)l</tt>/
*:[[Rhymes:English:-ɛt(ə)l|Rhymes: -ɛt(ə)l]]
===Noun===
'''kettle''' (''plural'' '''kettles''')
# A vessel for boiling water and other liquids.
#: ''There was a hot kettle of soup on the stove.''
# {''British'') A vessel for boiling [[tea]].
#: ''Stick the kettle on and we'll have a nice cup of tea.''
# A cooking pot used to steam fish.
====Usage note====
In British English, if not specified otherwise, the kettle usually refers to the use of the vessel for boiling the water for tea. The person saying it will also expect the person whom they are saying it to to brew the tea also.
: ''Stick the kettle on for us, [[son]].''
: ''Yes [[mum]]. One cup of tea, coming right up.''
====Derived terms====
*[[kettle of fish]]
*[[teakettle]] or [[tea kettle]]

